Popular clergyman, David Ibiyeomie, has ordered internet fraudsters popularly known as Yahoo boys to quit their ‘demonic’ exploits while laying a curse on them. The founder/presiding pastor of Salvation Ministries on Friday, in a video of his sermon titled: “Prophetic Declaration against internet fraudsters”, shared on his Instagram page, said no matter how much Yahoo boys try to sugar-coat their activities; it still boils down to stealing. The clergyman, who frowned at Yahoo boys, described their enterprise as a demonic/satanic way of making money which leads people to their graves daily.   Daddy Showkey to launch indigenous interaction app     Falz, Timaya, Skales storm Yung Willis private birthday in…     Let me die if I can’t take bullet for Davido, says PA   He said: “Yahoo boys, stop! You can’t be defrauding people every day. Stop! Listen, I am a man of God, stop!! - Advertisement - “You kill people every day. When you Yahoo somebody, it’s stealing. Don’t quote it anyhow, it’s stealing. “Most people all their retirement money, you take if from them and the people died. I curse you in the name of Jesus. “Listen, Stop! Stop! If you cannot bring a good name to Nigeria. Stop! If you’re in this church, stop! “It’s a demonic, satanic way of getting money.”